-- America Movil, BM&FBovespa: Latin America Equity Preview
-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   R a g i r
-- 2010-10-05T09:20:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/america-movil-bm-fbovespa-petrobras-latin-america-stock-markets-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The  MSCI Latin America Index  was little changed at
4,444.10. In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-
traded class of stock.  Brazil  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS): Brazil’s state-
controlled oil producer said output of oil and natural- gas
equivalent in Brazil and abroad rose to 2.599 million barrels a
day in August. Petrobras fell 0.4 percent to 27.38 reais.       BM&FBovespa SA  (BVMF3 BS): Brazil doubled a tax it charges
foreigners on investment in fixed-income securities in a bid to
stem gains in the real, which reached its strongest level in
more than two years last week, Finance Minister Guido Mantega
said. BM&FBovespa, the owner of the operator of Brazil’s biggest
securities exchange, rose 0.4 percent to 14.09 reais.  Mexico  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM): Latin America’s biggest
mobile-phone carrier got the licenses for wireless airwaves it
won in a July auction, the Mexican government said. The
Communications and Transportation Ministry announced the
handover of the licenses in an e-mailed statement today. America
Movil rose 0.7 percent to 34.20 reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
